msItem.note:
Receipt and quitclaim from Henry Wyat, knight, to Edmund Whyte, esquire, for £20 
                        for the purchase (pro perquisitione) of the manor of Parva Thorpe (Little Thorp)
                        Norfolk; Apr. 30, 1529.

Receipt of William Lakenham, prior of St Andrew's, Bromholm (Bromeholm),
                        for 40s. from John Jettoner, farmer of a moiety of the tithes of Carlton Colville (Carleton Colvyll),
                        Suffolk; Jan. 30, 1531.

Acquittance by sir Edw. North, chancellor of the court of augmentations,
                       for half a years fee received of the dean and chapter of Christ Church,
                       Oxford; June 22d 1554. (English)
